Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE is pleased to offer 387-397 Macquarie Street, Liverpool for sale via an Expressions of Interest.

387-397 Macquarie Street presents the rare opportunity to acquire a development project in Liverpool CBD with an existing development approval for 162 residential apartments and 6 retail/commercial suites.

Unit Mix:
1Bed = 37
2Bed = 115
3Bed = 10

The existing improvements on the property are a set of commercial strata suites, currently occupied by retail provides Cash Converters, Radio Rentals, and Motor Cycle Accessories Supermarket -all leases due to expire by Quarter 1 2017.

Liverpool is a forerunner for the housing, infrastructure, and employment growth being experienced throughout Western Sydney - set to be the capital of South West Sydney. During the next 10 years Liverpool will gain more infrastructure than any other city in Australia, and is being position as Sydney's third major city.

The Expressions of Interest campaign is scheduled to close on Thursday, the 27th of October 2016 at 3:00pm.

For more information please contact the dedicated CBRE team.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: LIVERPOOL CBD - DA Approved 162 Units + 6 Commercial

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
CBRE is pleased to present this rare and diverse opportunity at 274 George Street, Liverpool for sale via Public Auction on Saturday 3rd of March 2018 at 10:00am.

274 George Street Liverpool is a two level freehold commercial building in the heart of South West Sydney’s capital - Liverpool. Retail property in the Liverpool CBD seldom presents itself to the market for sale and this provides the opportunity to acquire a very sought-after asset. The Property is positioned in the south-eastern quarter of the CBD, providing close access to Liverpool Station, “Eat Street”, Bigge Park, Western Sydney University (opening 3rd March 2018), University of Wollongong and many more local attractions.

Having good neighbours is always important. Next door we have the new Western Sydney Airport Corporation, Quest Hotels, and the 10,000 m2 commercial building leased by the NSW Government.


The key property highlights are as follows: 

- Extremely versatile holding suiting an investor, developer or owner occupier  
- Current zoning of B3 Commercial Core with a B4 Mixed Use Pending
- Total land area of 194.7sqm* with dual access from Railway Serviceway 
- Existing net income of $58,000 with strategic opportunity leases 
- Total lettable area of 194.7sqm*, split in two levels providing ability of dual income or half occupation and income
- 4 on grade parking spots 
- Pending zoning allows for a small scale, “fine grain” development opportunity such as “student accommodation” or residential units without site amalgamation (subject to council approval and rezoning) 

Public Auction will be held on Saturday – 3rd March 2018 at 10:00am 

Auction Location: On site  

For further details please contact the below listed agents; 

Ned Mannoun - 0425 25 25 05

Thomas Mosca - 0423 086 593

*Approx.

Note: all reference to development potential for 274 George Street, Liverpool is subject to council approval and general in use only. We recommend you conduct your own investigation prior to purchasing this property. CBRE or it’s representatives take no responsibility for the accuracy of this information.

The Auction will be held at Auctionworks, Mezzanine Level, 50 Margaret Street, Sydney.

To obtain further information, please contact the listed agents.
